developer_response.body:
To cope with nausea - please consider the following:
- Adjust "Dynamic Comfort mode" bar in the settings and set it to the max; 
- In our experience, motion sickness ceases to be a problem relatively quickly if you give yourself and the game a chance;
- During the adjustment period - try to limit your gaming sessions in VR. Make them shorter, even if more frequent than usual;
- It has been proved that chewing gum reduces visually induced motion sickness: https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s00221-021-06303-5
- Try playing with a fan facing you in the same room as you play.

Please make sure that you are making proper use of your Squadron. We have prepared a guide, that might be helpful - https://www.homenetgames.com/warplanes-battles-over-pacific/article/bop-squadron-guide/
This mechanic and interface is basically analogous to Warplanes: WW1 Fighters.

Additionally, there are a few things that you could also take into consideration:
- You deal more damage the closer you are. Please make sure that you are firing when you are close enough that the HP bar of an enemy is visible;
- To reload faster - please hit the lever on the right of your machine gun(s) - most in-game weapons have those;
- There is always the “arcade mode” where you can take advantage of additional targeting assist. Just hold down your left trigger and the red crosshair will appear on your closest target. That will make aiming a lot easier.

